title: Shameless
description: From producers John Wells and Paul Abbott, this outrageous family drama is based on the long-running hit UK series and stars Emmy winner William H. Macy (Fargo) as a working class patriarch of an unconventional Chicago brood of six kids headed by the eldest sibling (Golden Globe nominee Emmy Rossum - Mystic River) who keep the home afloat while their dad is out drinking and carousing.

title: Batman: The Brave and the Bold
description: Batman fights evil in Gotham City and beyond, teaming up with various heroes from across the DC Comics universe.

title: Lincoln Heights
description: An L.A. cop moves his family from the suburbs to the inner-city neighborhood where he grew up. Their new surroundings aren't so welcoming, however, as they deal with drugs, crime and violence, and the kids have trouble adjusting at school.

title: Live From Lincoln Center
description: Classical selections, dance, opera, jazz and other music from New York's Lincoln Center. Winner of numerous Emmys and two Peabody Awards, it's one of TV's most durable cultural showcases. In 1976, the year of its debut, it featured the first live telecasts of a full-length ballet and a subtitled opera; and since has included numerous performances by the New York Philharmonic and such greats as Renee Fleming, James Galway, Wynton Marsalis, Luciano Pavarotti, Itzhak Perlman and Beverly Sills.
genres: John Goberman, Andrew C. Wilk, Rob Cavallo, Josh Groban, Esther Somlo, Livia Tortella

title: Him & Her
description: A comedy that takes an honest and unflinching look at the love between a working-class couple.

title: You Me Her
description: A comedy about a polyamorous relationship that develops between a suburban couple and an escort.
genres: Alan Gasmer, Peter Jaysen, Armand Leo, John Morayniss, John Scott Shepherd

title: Heroes
description: A drama delving into the lives of people from around the world who have superpowers, which they use to prevent a catastrophic future.

title: I'm Dying Up Here
description: Comedians struggle to make it big in the Los Angeles comedy scene of the 1970s.

title: Wild Kratts
description: A look at animals in their natural habitats. Also explores key scientific concepts that the animals' actions and behaviours display.
premiere: Vince Commisso, Martin Kratt, Steve Jarosz

title: Jack Hanna's Wild Countdown
description: Wildlife expert Jack Hanna presents Top 10 lists about the animal kingdom and shares his adventures from around the world.

title: Running Wild With Bear Grylls
description: Celebrities' survival skills are tested when they accompany an adventurer into remote locations around the world.
genres: Bear Grylls, Ben Silverman, Chris Grant, Laura Caraccioli, Doug McCallie, Viki Cacciatore, Corie Henson

description: A search for the most dangerous creatures on Earth.

description: Exploring how the staff at a wildlife park care for the exotic animals residing there.

title: Wildfire
description: After leaving a juvenile-detention center, a teen girl works with horses on a California ranch.

description: A series of sketches, interviews and stand-up routines featuring comedian Amy Schumer.

description: Comedian Amy Sedaris invites viewers into her home to show off her diverse homemaking skills.

description: A sitcom following the lives of a group of detectives in a New York precinct, including one slacker who is forced to shape up when he gets a new boss.
